title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare French MAS MLE 1949 - 56 IN 7.5 MM - NICE 49/56, similar to .308
postcontent: Here is a seldom seen collectible and functional military rifle. A French MAS MLE 1949-56 rifle in original 7.5 mm (it's listed as 7.62 NATO due to that being the closest option available). It includes many of the accessories that most others for sale don't include and are pricey as well as quite hard to come by. It has the original 'night sight' tube that slides over the end of the barrel, original sling with original cleaning kit and fully functional, adjustable sights as well as the flip up grenade launcher sights.Here's a little bit of info about this rifle's history:The predecessor rifle was the French MAS-49; it was formally adopted by the French Army in July 1949. An improved version of the MAS-49 was the MAS-49/56; it was introduced in 1957 and incorporated lessons learned from service in Algeria, Indochina, and the Suez Crisis. The rifle was shortened and lightened to improve mobility for mechanized and airborne troops, and a knife bayonet was added. The MAS-49 built-in rifle grenade launcher was replaced by a combination compensator/rifle grenade launcher that fired NATO-standard 22mm rifle grenades. The rifle also incorporates an integral grenade launching sight that is attached to the front sight block and a gas cutoff that prevents gas from entering the gas tube from the gas port when firing grenade launching blank ammunition.This rifle is chambered in the original 7.5 mm; many were re-chambered at import into .308 and are considered less desirable. Even though this is a very collectable rifle, it's a very fun weapon to shoot and will surprise you with how modern and well made it is. This rifle is in excellent overall condition. Tight action, clean barrel, and nice rifling. The stock in very good condition (see pictures). Again, weapon is in original 7.5 X 54 (French) or 7.5 mm, and also has the original barrel length at approximately 20.7". 3 original 10 round magazines included. This is a unique opportunity to own a fairly rare rifle in excellent condition and all the accessories included. Here's a little info about this very capable, but often overlooked caliber:The 7.5x54mm French rifle round was originally adopted for the French infantry to replace the aging 8mm Lebel. The French learned many lessons from World War I, and realized the need to adopt a more modern cartridge. In 1929 the 7.5x54 ammo cartridge was adopted by the French military along with the Mas 36 rifle.The 7.5 French cartridge served during World War II in various bullet configurations including ball, tracer, and incendiary. The bullet weight varies from 139 grain to 181 grain with velocities generally ranging from 2,700 feet per second to 2,600 feet per second. Although this round is older in design, it does features some impressive ballistics, especially when considering the round is not typically a shoulder bruiser.The round is capable of being an effective hunting cartridge at intermediate ranges, and is quite capable against medium to medium large North American game. The cartridge is particularly popular with military surplus enthusiasts, but not for the MAS 36 rifle, but for the MAS 49. The Mas 49 is an interesting semi-automatic, post-war rifle. In short, the 7.5mm French cartridge is an excellent cartridge that was an excellent wartime round that often gets overlooked.Included in the package are: rifle, 3 original 10 round magazines, original 'night sight' tube and canvas storage bag, 2 original magazine pouches (each hold 2 magazines), original sling with original cleaning kit attached and about 45 rounds of ammo (10 rounds of quality 'FOM' non corrosive, 20 reloads + about 15 rounds of Turkish corrosive ammo). Ammo is available for this rifle and I can offer you my cost for more rounds if desired.Thank youtags: CETME, HK91, FN FAL, .308Will trade for:Feel free to ask any questions and offer any trades or cash + trade offers. I own an extensive collection of fine weapons and have worked at a gun shop before so please don't bother me by asking a ridiculous amount in trade for what you have.I can transfer this to your local FFL for the cost of shipping, no extra 'handling or shipping fees'.

title: For Sale:  AR15 trigger work (service) NOT A PART
postcontent: After getting numerous requests from people I have decided to post an ad for AR trigger work. Below is what will be required and what will be done. Price will be a flat $25 with free shipping back to you. Required-Your AR trigger, disconnector and hammer.What will be done is quite simple in theory but does take meticulous work to really clean it up.What will be done-Overall function check on trigger jig for safety. If I find it to be unsafe I will decline work or offer to replace the defunct part. Safety is key.-All contact surfaces checked for burr's and cleaned up-Check for and get rid of machining marks from factory-End with a high gloss-smooth as silk polish on all contact points-Lightly lubed with Aeroshell 6 grease. I'm out of tiny sample grease contaniers at the moment that I would normally just send back to you.-This job will not alter any angles or remove any safety from the trigger assembly. It's amazing how you can turn a regular mil spec trigger into something a lot better for not a lot of money. AR trigger's usually all have machining marks that go AGAINST the normal pull on the trigger. Machining marks are bad enough;one's that go the wrong way are even worse.Please feel free to email me and ask any questions. I look forward to getting to work!
